<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-12T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-12T01:00:00-05:00" n="837" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102H/327: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-12T14:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">July 12,
                                        1919—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 12—9:55
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your July 2, 4 p.m., my June 20 [<hi rend="italic">21</hi>], 12 noon.
                            American firm in question is Standard Oil Company which today reports
                            cannot further delay action without losing site for which other
                            interests are competing. They request decision as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>